The paper deals with the fine-grained complexity of classical problems in computer science, which suggests that it would likely fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The problems studied involve graph algorithms (such as All-Pairs Shortest Paths, Diameter, and Radius) and optimization problems (such as Knapsack), which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves some combinatorial aspects, such as finding the parity of a solution, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT).
